{"title_page": "Terry Ward", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Terry Ward\n| image          = \n| fullname       = Terence Ward<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| birth_date    = 10 December 1939<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| birth_place = [[Stoke-on-Trent]], England<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| death_date    = 1963 (aged 23)<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| death_place = [[Stoke-on-Trent]], England<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| years1         = 1959\u20131963| clubs1 = [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] | caps1 = 43 | goals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Terence''' \"'''Terry'''\" '''Ward''' (10 December 1939 \u2013 1963) was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played in [[the Football League]] for [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] along with his brother [[Derrick Ward (footballer)|Derrick]].<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\">{{cite book|last=Matthews|first=Tony|title=The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City|year=1994|publisher=Lion Press|isbn=0-9524151-0-0}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nWard was born in [[Stoke-on-Trent]] and joined the local [[the Football League|Football League]] club [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] in 1959 where his brother [[Derrick Ward (footballer)|Derrick]] had been since 1952.<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/> He made his debut during the [[1959\u201360 Stoke City F.C. season|1959\u201360 season]] and broke into the squad in the [[1960\u201361 Stoke City F.C. season|following season]] playing in 29 matches.<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/> However it was around this time that Ward started to suffer from ill health and after two seasons of struggling to get into the side he decided to retire.<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/> Not long after he left the club his health problems escalated and he died at the age of 23.<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|FA Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]]<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n|[[1959\u201360 Stoke City F.C. season|1959\u201360]]\n|[[Football League Second Division|Second Division]]\n|3||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||3||0\n|-\n|[[1960\u201361 Stoke City F.C. season|1960\u201361]]\n|Second Division\n|27||0||1||0||1||0||29||0\n|-\n|[[1961\u201362 Stoke City F.C. season|1961\u201362]]\n|Second Division\n|4||0||0||0||0||0||4||0\n|-\n|[[1962\u201363 Stoke City F.C. season|1962\u201363]]\n|Second Division\n|9||0||0||0||1||0||10||0\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career Total\n!43!!0!!1!!0!!2!!0!!46!!0\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ward, Terry}}\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Stoke City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:1939 births]]\n[[Category:1963 deaths]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Stoke-on-Trent]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Terry Ward\n| image          = \n| fullname       = Terence Ward<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| birth_date    = 10 December 1939<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| birth_place = [[Stoke-on-Trent]], England<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| death_date    = 1963 (aged 23)<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| death_place = [[Stoke-on-Trent]], England<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n| position       = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| years1         = 1959\u20131963| clubs1 = [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] | caps1 = 43 | goals1 = 0\n}}\n'''Terence''' \"'''Terry'''\" '''Ward''' (10 December 1939 \u2013 1963) was an English [[association football|footballer]] who played in [[the Football League]] for [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] along with his brother [[Derrick Ward (footballer)|Derrick]].<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\">{{cite book|last=Matthews|first=Tony|title=The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City|year=1994|publisher=Lion Press|isbn=0-9524151-0-0}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nWard was born in [[Stoke-on-Trent]] and joined the local [[the Football League|Football League]] club [[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]] in 1959 where his brother [[Derrick Ward (footballer)|Derrick]] had been since 1952.<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/> He made his debut during the [[1959\u201360 Stoke City F.C. season|1959\u201360 season]] and broke into the squad in the [[1960\u201361 Stoke City F.C. season|following season]] playing in 29 matches.<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/> However it was around this time that Ward started to suffer from ill health and after two seasons of struggling to get into the side he decided to retire.<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/> Not long after he left the club his health problems escalated and he died at the age of 23.<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|FA Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|[[Stoke City F.C.|Stoke City]]<ref name=\"The Encyclopaedia of Stoke City\"/>\n|[[1959\u201360 Stoke City F.C. season|1959\u201360]]\n|[[Football League Second Division|Second Division]]\n|3||0||0||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2013||3||0\n|-\n|[[1960\u201361 Stoke City F.C. season|1960\u201361]]\n|Secon